b'Graduate Medical Education (GME)'
b'Family Medicine Residency Welcome'
b'Rockford Family Medicine Residency Program'
b'tlowery1'
b'Salary/Benefits'
b'Salary (2018-2019)'
b'Resident stipends for the academic year of 2018-2019 are as follows: R1 $53,307 R2 $55,000 R3 $57,000 Chief Resident $59,000'
b'Other benefits include: \xe2\x80\xa2 Relocation allowance up to $1,500 (R1) \xe2\x80\xa2 Laptop \xe2\x80\xa2 Free access to UptoDate, MD Consult and all University of Illinois library resources \xe2\x80\xa2 Meals provided when on duty in the hospital \xe2\x80\xa2 Lab coats and laundry service \xe2\x80\xa2 Life insurance \xe2\x80\x93 1x salary, with option to purchase additional term life coverage for spouse and children \xe2\x80\xa2 Health, dental and vision insurance \xe2\x80\xa2 Tax-deferred voluntary savings plan \xe2\x80\xa2 Membership at the YMCA for resident \xe2\x80\xa2 Subsidized on-site child care \xe2\x80\xa2 Family leave \xe2\x80\xa2 Professional liability insurance coverage related to residency program duties \xe2\x80\xa2 Paid certification courses in ALSO, NRP, and ACLS \xe2\x80\xa2 Twenty-one days of paid time off per year \xe2\x80\xa2 Five additional days per year available for conference attendance \xe2\x80\xa2 $700 (R1)/$1,200 (R2/R3) CME funding per year available for conference attendance, medical books or software \xe2\x80\xa2 Medical library with free photocopy privileges \xe2\x80\xa2 Annual retreat \xe2\x80\xa2 Night float call system \xe2\x80\xa2 Hospital call rooms provided \xe2\x80\xa2 Opportunity for a Masters in Public Health certificate \xe2\x80\xa2 Access to Glenn Netto Health and Wellness Center \xe2\x80\xa2 Access to the UIC Health Sciences Campus-Rockford Outside employment is permissible with the consent of the program director. Presently, there is opportunity for third-year residents to moonlight in local emergency rooms and after-hours clinics. Residents must first obtain an Illinois permanent license.'
